    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>QUALCOMM BUYS EATON TRUCKING UNIT</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Simon Romero</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Romero, Simon</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Qualcomm, in move to strengthen its fleet management business, acquires Eaton Corp's trucking information services unit, FleetAdvisor, for undisclosed amount of cash and payments based on future sales; Qualcomm plans to use unit to improve services like automated trucker logs and fuel tax calculation (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>In a move to strengthen its fleet management business, Qualcomm has agreed to acquire the Eaton Corporation's trucking information services unit for an undisclosed amount of cash and for payments based on future sales. Qualcomm plans to use the unit, called FleetAdvisor, to improve services like automated driver logs and fuel tax calculation. Under the agreement, Qualcomm has hired about 40 employees from Eaton, which is based in Cleveland.</p>
        <p>Simon Romero (NYT)</p>
      </block>
